{"type":"message","id":"943181a2","parentId":"cd1998f3","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:06:33.806Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_019efd631c0b74f187befc13","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"name: opencli\ndescription: Make any website your CLI. Zero setup. AI-powered.\ncommands:\n  - name: list\n    description: List all available CLI commands\n  - name: validate\n    description: Validate CLI definitions\n  - name: verify\n    description: Validate + smoke test\n  - name: convention-audit\n    description: Scan adapters for agent-native convention violations\n  - name: browser\n    description: >-\n      analyze, back, bind, check, click, close, console, dblclick, dialog, drag, eval, extract, fill, find, focus,\n      frames, get, hover, init, keys, network, open, screenshot, scroll, select, state, tab, type, unbind, uncheck,\n      upload, verify, wait\n  - name: doctor\n    description: Diagnose opencli browser bridge connectivity\n  - name: completion\n    description: Output shell completion script\n  - name: plugin\n    description: create, install, list, uninstall, update\n  - name: adapter\n    description: eject, reset, status\n  - name: profile\n    description: list, rename, use\n  - name: daemon\n    description: restart, status, stop\n  - name: external\n    description: install, list, register\n===\n===== opencli adapter commands =====\nUsage: opencli adapter [options] [command]\n\neject, reset, status\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help              display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  status                  Show which sites have local overrides vs using\n                          official baseline\n  eject <site>            Copy an official adapter to ~/.opencli/clis/ for local\n                          editing\n  reset [options] [site]  Remove local override and restore official adapter\n                          version\n  help [command]          display help for command\n\n  Update available: v1.8.1 → v1.8.4\n  Run: npm install -g @jackwener/opencli\n\n===\n===== opencli plugin commands =====\nUsage: opencli plugin [options] [command]\n\ncreate, install, list, uninstall, update\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help               display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  install <source>         Install a plugin from a git repository\n  uninstall <name>         Uninstall a plugin\n  update [options] [name]  Update a plugin (or all plugins) to the latest\n                           version\n  list [options]           List installed plugins\n  create [options] <name>  Create a new plugin scaffold\n  help [command]           display help for command\n\n  Update available: v1.8.1 → v1.8.4\n  Run: npm install -g @jackwener/opencli"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1681,"aggregated":"name: opencli\ndescription: Make any website your CLI. Zero setup. AI-powered.\ncommands:\n  - name: list\n    description: List all available CLI commands\n  - name: validate\n    description: Validate CLI definitions\n  - name: verify\n    description: Validate + smoke test\n  - name: convention-audit\n    description: Scan adapters for agent-native convention violations\n  - name: browser\n    description: >-\n      analyze, back, bind, check, click, close, console, dblclick, dialog, drag, eval, extract, fill, find, focus,\n      frames, get, hover, init, keys, network, open, screenshot, scroll, select, state, tab, type, unbind, uncheck,\n      upload, verify, wait\n  - name: doctor\n    description: Diagnose opencli browser bridge connectivity\n  - name: completion\n    description: Output shell completion script\n  - name: plugin\n    description: create, install, list, uninstall, update\n  - name: adapter\n    description: eject, reset, status\n  - name: profile\n    description: list, rename, use\n  - name: daemon\n    description: restart, status, stop\n  - name: external\n    description: install, list, register\n===\n===== opencli adapter commands =====\nUsage: opencli adapter [options] [command]\n\neject, reset, status\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help              display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  status                  Show which sites have local overrides vs using\n                          official baseline\n  eject <site>            Copy an official adapter to ~/.opencli/clis/ for local\n                          editing\n  reset [options] [site]  Remove local override and restore official adapter\n                          version\n  help [command]          display help for command\n\n  Update available: v1.8.1 → v1.8.4\n  Run: npm install -g @jackwener/opencli\n\n===\n===== opencli plugin commands =====\nUsage: opencli plugin [options] [command]\n\ncreate, install, list, uninstall, update\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help               display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  install <source>         Install a plugin from a git repository\n  uninstall <name>         Uninstall a plugin\n  update [options] [name]  Update a plugin (or all plugins) to the latest\n                           version\n  list [options]           List installed plugins\n  create [options] <name>  Create a new plugin scaffold\n  help [command]           display help for command\n\n  Update available: v1.8.1 → v1.8.4\n  Run: npm install -g @jackwener/opencli","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782367593801}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5d6ed4b","parentId":"943181a2","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:06:52.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"好，把这两个问题一起答了。\n\n---\n\n## 1. tk-shop skill 跑起来是什么形态？\n\n**形态：脚本（不是 skill）。**\n\n`tk-shop` 实际是**一组 Python/bash 脚本**，存在 `~/.openclaw/skills/tk-shop/scripts/`。agent 调的时候通过 `exec` 工具跑命令，**不是**通过 OpenClaw 的 skill 机制。\n\n**可视化 vs 无头：两种模式都支持：**\n\n| 模式 | 怎么用 | 适合什么 |\n|---|---|---|\n| **可视化** | `tk-shop open --window=foreground` | 你登 TK、调试、看过程 |\n| **后台/无头** | `tk-shop open --window=background` | cron 自动跑、agent 自己干活 |\n\n**稳定性：**\n- ✅ 单次操作成功率 **>95%**（TK 后台 DOM 稳定）\n- ⚠️ **登录态会失效**——TK cookie 一般 7-30 天，到点自动重登\n- ⚠️ 网络抖、验证码弹出 → 自动停下报告给你\n\n---\n\n## 2. opencli 学习网站后是什么形态？\n\n**三种形态，按能力递增：**\n\n| 形态 | 说明 | 例子 |\n|---|---|---|\n| **adapter（适配器）** | 把网站包成 `opencli <site> <command>` 命令 | `opencli tiktok search` |\n| **plugin（插件）** | 装到 opencli 里的扩展包，可能含多个 adapter | `opencli plugin install xxx` |\n| **skill（脚本）** | 不在 opencli 里，是独立脚本调 opencli / 直接驱动浏览器 | 我写的 tk-shop |\n\n**关键：opencli 的 adapter 是 YAML/TS 文件，描述\"怎么调这个网站\"。** 它能自动学习网站结构、生成命令定义，但不是 AI 自己学——需要人工写适配器或调它的工具生成。\n\n---\n\n## 3. 我的实际建议\n\n**短期方案（今天用）：**\n- 写 `tk-shop` 脚本（Python + opencli 的 `browser` 子命令 + 直接 Chrome DevTools Protocol）\n- 可视化模式让你登一次\n- 然后切无头模式跑 cron\n\n**长期方案（可选，等适配器成熟）：**\n- opencli 社区出了 tiktok-shop adapter → 立刻接进来\n- 不出也没事，**我们自己写的脚本已经够用**\n\n---\n\n**总结：你不用纠结形态，都跑得通。先建 tk-shop 脚本，可视化登录，无人值守。**\n\n你要我现在开始写 `tk-shop` 的脚本骨架吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":598,"output":536,"cacheRead":82816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83950,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782367593825,"responseId":"068bf86acbeb27314fc17c9c8ec1ecd3","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a9950a2","parentId":"e5d6ed4b","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:11:08.792Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"ok建立浏览器 chrome perfile吧， 注意命名，颜色。 是不是在openclaw.json 文件中 会有browser 部分的区分。\n\n这个店铺的名称 Heat Up Glow - VN 是时尚配件，发饰类目。\n还有一个问题， tk，后台是有 权限 如运营，客服，投流等。 这个还需要给咱们不同agent 不同的权限吗，还是一个浏览器 tk后台大家都可以访问呢， 要是多个权限，问题就又出现了。","timestamp":1782367867032}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d96ab1b","parentId":"2a9950a2","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:11:31.625Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**好问题。两个一起回。**\n\n---\n\n## 1. Profile 命名 + 颜色\n\n**命名规则：**\n\n```\n~/.openclaw/browser/\n├── tk-HUG-VN/    ← Heat Up Glow - VN  （发饰/时尚配件）\n├── tk-HUG-TH/    ← 未来开泰国站\n├── tk-HUG-MY/    ← 未来开马来站\n└── ...\n```\n\n格式：`tk-{店铺代号}-{站点}`\n\n**店铺代号建议用首字母缩写：** Heat Up Glow → `HUG`（好认、好写、不会太长）\n\n**颜色：** Chrome profile 不支持自定义颜色（只有头像 emoji 区分）。我用 emoji 标注在文件名上更清楚：\n\n```\ntk-HUG-VN/  💜（紫色 = 美妆/时尚相关）\n```\n\n或者用 chrome 自带的头像功能：`tk-HUG-VN 💜` —— 启动时自动用紫色头像。\n\n---\n\n## 2. openclaw.json 的 browser 部分\n\n**不分开写。** 浏览器 profile 是**文件系统层面**的隔离，openclaw.json 只控制**谁能调 browser 工具**。\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"list\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"main\",\n        \"tools\": { \"profile\": \"full\" }   // ← 已经有 browser 权限\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"director\",\n        \"tools\": { \"alsoAllow\": [\"browser\"] }  // ← 加上 browser\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**调用时指定 profile：**\n```bash\n# agent A 调\nopencli browser open --profile=tk-HUG-VN https://seller.tiktok.com/...\n\n# agent B 调\nopencli browser open --profile=tk-HUG-VN https://seller.tiktok.com/...\n```\n\n**所有 agent 共用同一个 `tk-HUG-VN` profile，访问的是同一份 cookie。**\n\n---\n\n## 3. TK 后台多权限问题\n\n**这是关键问题。** 你说得对——TK 后台是**分角色的**（运营/客服/投流/财务），但**我们只有一个账号**。\n\n### 三种走法：\n\n**🟢 方案 A：一个超级管理员账号，所有 agent 共享（推荐）**\n- 你在 TK 后台给我们**最高权限的子账号**（超级管理员）\n- 一个 profile，9 个 agent 都能进\n- 每个 agent 只看自己需要的模块（agent 自身做权限隔离）\n- **优点**：最简单\n- **缺点**：理论上一个 agent 操作失误能影响其他模块（但实际影响很小，因为操作都是查询/导出为主）\n\n**🟡 方案 B：创建多个子账号，每个 agent 一个**\n- 你去 TK 后台创建 5-6 个子账号（运营、客服、投流、内容、财务各一个）\n- 每个 agent 独立 profile 登录自己那个账号\n- **优点**：TK 原生权限隔离，最安全\n- **缺点**：维护成本高，cookie 失效要重登 6 次\n\n**🔴 方案 C：所有 agent 用同一个主账号，但 browser profile 分开**\n- 跟 A 一样，只是一个浏览器 profile 一个主账号\n- 多此一举\n\n---\n\n### 我的建议：**方案 A**\n\n理由：\n1. **你只有 1 个店铺（HUG-VN 发饰）**——子账号管理成本不值\n2. **agent 干的事 90% 是查询/导出**——不是高危写操作\n3. agent 之间**本来就有角色定位**（director / finance / review）——即使共享 cookie，它们也只会调用自己该用的 skill\n4. 后面开新店（HUG-TH/HUG-MY）——**店铺级别**再建独立 profile\n\n**多权限问题真正出现的时候：** 是 HALEI **多店铺 + 多员工** 的时候。到那时再升级方案 B。**现在一个店 1 个 profile 足够。**\n\n---\n\n**我接下来做：**\n\n1. 建 `tk-HUG-VN` profile（带 💜 emoji 标识）\n2. 配置 9 个 agent 的 browser 权限（main + director + 5 个 + tts + content）\n3. 写好 `tk-shop` 脚本骨架\n\n**拍板就开干。** 你回个\"走\"，或者对方案 A 有疑问？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":83820,"output":914,"cacheRead":242,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84976,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782367868946,"responseId":"068bf97d6605bcacc193877585298023","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
