{"type":"message","id":"a1cf5edf","parentId":"a9f5cbfe","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:15:52.082Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_019efd6b802878f19a633efb","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session delta-basil, pid 1726964). Use process (list/poll/log/write/send-keys/submit/paste/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"delta-basil","pid":1726964,"startedAt":1782368141826,"cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace","tail":"iguration-reference#browser)).\\n  - Role snapshot options (`--interactive`, `--compact`, `--depth`, `--selector`) force a role-based snapshot with refs like `ref=e12`.\\n  - `--frame \\\"<iframe selector>\\\"` scopes role snapshots to an iframe (pairs with role refs like `e12`).\\n  - `--interactive` outputs a flat, easy-to-pick list of interactive elements (best for driving actions).\\n  - `--labels` adds a viewport-only screenshot with overlayed ref labels (prints `MEDIA:<path>`).\\n- `click`/`type`/etc require a `ref` from `snapshot` (either numeric `12` or role ref `e12`).\\n  CSS selectors are intentionally not supported for actions.\\n\\n## Snapshots and refs\\n\\nOpenClaw supports two “snapshot” styles:\\n\\n- **AI snapshot (numeric refs)**: `openclaw browser snapshot` (default; `--format ai`)\\n  - Output: a text snapshot that includes numeric refs.\\n  - Actions: `openclaw browser click 12`, `openclaw browser type 23 \\\"hello\\\"`.\\n  - Internally, the ref is resolved via Playwright’s `aria-ref`.\\n\\n- **Role snapshot (role refs like `e12`)**: `openclaw browser snapshot --interactive` (or `--compact`, `--depth`, `--selector`, `--frame`)\\n  - Output: a role-based list/tree with `[ref=e12]` (and optional `[nth=1]`).\\n  - Actions: `openclaw browser click e12`, `openclaw browser highlight e12`.\\n  - Internally, the ref is resolved via `getByRole(...)` (plus `nth()` for duplicates).\\n  - Add `--labels` to include a viewport screenshot with overlayed `e12` labels.\\n\\nRef behavior:\\n\\n- Refs are **not stable across navigations**; if something fails, re-run `snapshot` and use a fresh ref.\\n- If the role snapshot was taken with `--frame`, role refs are scoped to that iframe until the next role snapshot.\\n\\n## Wait power-ups\\n\\nYou can wait on more than just time/text:\\n\\n- Wait for URL (globs supported by Playwright):\\n  - `openclaw browser wait --url \\\"**/dash\\\"`\\n- Wait for load state:\\n  - `openclaw browser wait --load networkidle`\\n- Wait for a JS predicate:\\n  - `openclaw browser w"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782368152074}}
{"type":"message","id":"63774885","parentId":"a1cf5edf","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:15:58.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_019efd6bc3c4782195eae559","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"delta-basil","timeout":15000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":177,"output":49,"cacheRead":86400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86626,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782368152175,"responseId":"068bfa99c74c081d1653e61965ec057b","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c30dbce","parentId":"63774885","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:15:59.315Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_019efd6bc3c4782195eae559","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"refer narrow host exceptions such as `hostnameAllowlist` or `allowedHostnames` over broad private-network access.\\n- Use `dangerouslyAllowPrivateNetwork: true` only in intentionally trusted environments where private-network browser access is required and reviewed.\\n\\nExample: navigation blocked, control plane healthy\\n\\n- `start` succeeds\\n- `tabs` succeeds\\n- `open http://internal.example` fails\\n\\nThat usually means browser startup is fine and the navigation target needs policy review.\\n\\nExample: startup blocked before navigation matters\\n\\n- `start` fails with `not reachable after start`\\n- `tabs` also fails or cannot run\\n\\nThat points to browser launch or CDP reachability, not a page URL allowlist problem.\\n\\n## Agent tools + how control works\\n\\nThe agent gets **one tool** for browser automation:\\n\\n- `browser` — status/start/stop/tabs/open/focus/close/snapshot/screenshot/navigate/act\\n\\nHow it maps:\\n\\n- `browser snapshot` returns a stable UI tree (AI or ARIA).\\n- `browser act` uses the snapshot `ref` IDs to click/type/drag/select.\\n- `browser screenshot` captures pixels (full page or element).\\n- `browser` accepts:\\n  - `profile` to choose a named browser profile (openclaw, chrome, or remote CDP).\\n  - `target` (`sandbox` | `host` | `node`) to select where the browser lives.\\n  - In sandboxed sessions, `target: \\\"host\\\"` requires `agents.defaults.sandbox.browser.allowHostControl=true`.\\n  - If `target` is omitted: sandboxed sessions default to `sandbox`, non-sandbox sessions default to `host`.\\n  - If a browser-capable node is connected, the tool may auto-route to it unless you pin `target=\\\"host\\\"` or `target=\\\"node\\\"`.\\n\\nThis keeps the agent deterministic and avoids brittle selectors.\\n\\n## Related\\n\\n- [Tools Overview](/tools) — all available agent tools\\n- [Sandboxing](/gateway/sandboxing) — browser control in sandboxed environments\\n- [Security](/gateway/security) — browser control risks and hardening\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1776340688108}}\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","sessionId","exitCode","aggregated","name"],"status":"completed","sessionId":"delta-basil","name":"echo ===== try clawpanel device key =====","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782368159305}}
{"type":"message","id":"31e25d37","parentId":"0c30dbce","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:16:19.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"我搜到的是 OpenClaw 文档说明。截图里的 `profiles.work` / `profiles.personal` 段——**实际 openclaw.json 里没有**。这张截图可能是你从某个**教程或参考**拿来的，不是你现在的实际配置。\n\n实际当前配置：\n```json\n\"browser\": { \"headless\": false }\n```\n\n只有 headless 一个字段。**profiles 段根本不存在。**\n\n---\n\n## 🪶 那现在的真实情况是这样\n\n**OpenClaw 6.9 的 `browser` 工具**支持 `profile` 参数来切换浏览器 profile（openclaw / chrome / 远程 CDP），但**openclaw.json 里没有定义 profiles 段**。\n\n要让 HUG-VN 真正可用，**有两条路：**\n\n| 方案 | 怎么做 | 优点 | 缺点 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **A. 用 OpenClaw 自带 `browser` 工具的 profile 机制** | 通过 `profile` 参数指定，不写 openclaw.json | 零配置，立即可用 | profile 不是 JSON 段定义，靠工具默认 |\n| **B. 自己写完整的 `browser.profiles` 段** | 改 openclaw.json，加 tk-HUG-VN 配置 | 显式、可控、配色可视化 | 需要改 openclaw.json 重启 gateway |\n\n**我建议走 B**——你既然提到了配置段和颜色，说明你想要的就是这种**显式管理**的方式。改 openclaw.json 重启 gateway 不复杂，我已经备过 .bak。\n\n---\n\n## 我准备做\n\n1. **改 openclaw.json 加 profiles 段**\n   ```json\n   \"browser\": {\n     \"headless\": false,\n     \"defaultProfile\": \"tk-HUG-VN\",\n     \"profiles\": {\n       \"tk-HUG-VN\": {\n         \"userDataDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/browser/tk-HUG-VN\",\n         \"cdpPort\": 18901,\n         \"color\": \"#A155F0\",\n         \"label\": \"Heat Up Glow - VN 💜\"\n       }\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **重启 gateway 加载新配置**（用 `gateway` 工具）\n\n3. **浏览器测试 profile 可用**\n\n4. **截图给你看**确认\n\n---\n\n**HALEI 我有几个问题：**\n\n- **配色用什么颜色？** 紫色 (#A155F0) 还是其他？你有偏好吗\n- **CDP 端口 18901 跟现有 18801/18802 不冲突**——这样行不行\n- **要不要加一个 work/personal profile？** 截图里那俩我可以一起补上（如果你本来就有用）\n\n你说，我就动。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":607,"output":560,"cacheRead":86528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782368159361,"responseId":"068bfa9fea7d5dc1a2112b577ac238b1","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
