{"type":"message","id":"1662693e","parentId":"e6ceb014","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:16:26.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"明白了——截图里那个 profiles 段是**别人**配置文件里的参考示例，不是你这边要复刻的格式。**我直接用 OpenClaw 6.9 的实际 schema 来写。**\n\n那直接开干。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xm0d9sd0ly6w_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"browser"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":86855,"output":84,"cacheRead":498,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87437,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782368181235,"responseId":"068bfab5d7edf7c8982c9a9f66c98ee9","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"575444f4","parentId":"1662693e","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:16:30.521Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xm0d9sd0ly6w_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"path\": \"browser\",\n    \"schema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"title\": \"Browser\",\n      \"description\": \"Browser runtime controls for local or remote CDP attachment, profile routing, and screenshot/snapshot behavior. Keep defaults unless your automation workflow requires custom browser transport settings.\"\n    },\n    \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n    \"hint\": {\n      \"label\": \"Browser\",\n      \"group\": \"Browser\",\n      \"order\": 130,\n      \"help\": \"Browser runtime controls for local or remote CDP attachment, profile routing, and screenshot/snapshot behavior. Keep defaults unless your automation workflow requires custom browser transport settings.\",\n      \"tags\": [\n        \"advanced\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"hintPath\": \"browser\",\n    \"children\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"enabled\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.enabled\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Enabled\",\n          \"help\": \"Enables browser capability wiring in the gateway so browser tools and CDP-driven workflows can run. Disable when browser automation is not needed to reduce surface area and startup work.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.enabled\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"evaluateEnabled\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.evaluateEnabled\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Evaluate Enabled\",\n          \"help\": \"Enables browser-side evaluate helpers for runtime script evaluation capabilities where supported. Keep disabled unless your workflows require evaluate semantics beyond snapshots/navigation.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.evaluateEnabled\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"cdpUrl\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.cdpUrl\",\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser CDP URL\",\n          \"help\": \"CDP/DevTools endpoint URL used to attach to an externally managed browser instance. Use this for centralized browser hosts, tunnels, or existing-session attachment, and keep URL access restricted to trusted network paths.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\",\n            \"url-secret\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.cdpUrl\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"remoteCdpTimeoutMs\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.remoteCdpTimeoutMs\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Remote CDP Timeout (ms)\",\n          \"help\": \"Timeout in milliseconds for connecting to a remote CDP endpoint before failing the browser attach attempt. Increase for high-latency tunnels, or lower for faster failure detection.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"performance\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.remoteCdpTimeoutMs\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"remoteCdpHandshakeTimeoutMs\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.remoteCdpHandshakeTimeoutMs\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Remote CDP Handshake Timeout (ms)\",\n          \"help\": \"Timeout in milliseconds for post-connect CDP handshake readiness checks against remote browser targets. Raise this for slow-start remote browsers and lower to fail fast in automation loops.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"performance\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.remoteCdpHandshakeTimeoutMs\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"localLaunchTimeoutMs\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.localLaunchTimeoutMs\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Local Launch Timeout (ms)\",\n          \"help\": \"Timeout in milliseconds for locally launched managed Chrome to expose its CDP HTTP endpoint after process start. Raise this on slow single-board computers or older hosts.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"performance\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.localLaunchTimeoutMs\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"localCdpReadyTimeoutMs\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.localCdpReadyTimeoutMs\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Local CDP Ready Timeout (ms)\",\n          \"help\": \"Timeout in milliseconds for a locally launched managed browser to finish CDP websocket readiness after the process is discovered. Raise this when Chrome starts but browser start still reports CDP not reachable.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"performance\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.localCdpReadyTimeoutMs\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"actionTimeoutMs\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.actionTimeoutMs\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Action Timeout (ms)\",\n          \"help\": \"Default timeout in milliseconds for browser act requests before the client gives up waiting. Raise this when healthy waits or UI interactions exceed the default request budget.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"performance\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.actionTimeoutMs\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"color\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.color\",\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Accent Color\",\n          \"help\": \"Default accent color used for browser profile/UI cues where colored identity hints are displayed. Use consistent colors to help operators identify active browser profile context quickly.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.color\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"executablePath\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.executablePath\",\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Executable Path\",\n          \"help\": \"Explicit browser executable path when auto-discovery is insufficient for your host environment. Use an absolute stable path, or a path starting with ~ for your OS home directory, so launch behavior stays deterministic across restarts.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"storage\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.executablePath\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"headless\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.headless\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Headless Mode\",\n          \"help\": \"Forces browser launch in headless mode when the local launcher starts browser instances. Keep headless enabled for server environments and disable only when visible UI debugging is required.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.headless\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"noSandbox\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.noSandbox\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser No-Sandbox Mode\",\n          \"help\": \"Disables Chromium sandbox isolation flags for environments where sandboxing fails at runtime. Keep this off whenever possible because process isolation protections are reduced.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"storage\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.noSandbox\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"attachOnly\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.attachOnly\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Attach-only Mode\",\n          \"help\": \"Restricts browser mode to attach-only behavior without starting local browser processes. Use this when all browser sessions are externally managed by a remote CDP provider.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.attachOnly\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"cdpPortRangeStart\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.cdpPortRangeStart\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser CDP Port Range Start\",\n          \"help\": \"Starting local CDP port used for auto-allocated browser profile ports. Increase this when host-level port defaults conflict with other local services.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.cdpPortRangeStart\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"defaultProfile\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.defaultProfile\",\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Default Profile\",\n          \"help\": \"Default browser profile name selected when callers do not explicitly choose a profile. Use a stable low-privilege profile as the default to reduce accidental cross-context state use.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"storage\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.defaultProfile\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"snapshotDefaults\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.snapshotDefaults\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Snapshot Defaults\",\n          \"help\": \"Default snapshot capture configuration used when callers do not provide explicit snapshot options. Tune this for consistent capture behavior across channels and automation paths.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.snapshotDefaults\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"ssrfPolicy\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.ssrfPolicy\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser SSRF Policy\",\n          \"help\": \"Server-side request forgery guardrail settings for browser/network fetch paths that could reach internal hosts. Keep restrictive defaults in production and open only explicitly approved targets.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"access\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.ssrfPolicy\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"profiles\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.profiles\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Profiles\",\n          \"help\": \"Named browser profile connection map used for explicit routing to CDP ports or URLs with optional metadata. Keep profile names consistent and avoid overlapping endpoint definitions.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"storage\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.profiles\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"extraArgs\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.extraArgs\",\n        \"type\": \"array\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"tabCleanup\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.tabCleanup\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Browser Tab Cleanup\",\n          \"help\": \"Best-effort cleanup policy for browser tabs opened by primary-agent sessions. Keep enabled to avoid stale sandbox or managed-browser tabs accumulating across long-lived gateways.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"advanced\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"browser.tabCleanup\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["ok","result"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782368190516}}
{"type":"message","id":"24519fe3","parentId":"575444f4","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:16:35.196Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**完美。** `browser.profiles` 是 OpenClaw 6.9 的官方配置项。**截图里那个格式基本是对的**——我按官方 schema 来写就行。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d3fq6e7kwiqn_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"browser.profiles"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":2753,"output":77,"cacheRead":87339,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90169,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782368190538,"responseId":"068bfabf431689255d88d1a0131a1794","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9699b306","parentId":"24519fe3","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:16:35.596Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d3fq6e7kwiqn_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"path\": \"browser.profiles\",\n    \"schema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"title\": \"Browser Profiles\",\n      \"description\": \"Named browser profile connection map used for explicit routing to CDP ports or URLs with optional metadata. Keep profile names consistent and avoid overlapping endpoint definitions.\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"cdpPort\": {\n            \"type\": \"integer\",\n            \"minimum\": 1,\n            \"maximum\": 65535,\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile CDP Port\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile local CDP port used when connecting to browser instances by port instead of URL. Use unique ports per profile to avoid connection collisions.\"\n          },\n          \"cdpUrl\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile CDP URL\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile CDP/DevTools endpoint URL used for explicit browser routing by profile name. Use this for remote CDP hosts, tunnels, or existing-session profiles that should attach through a running Chrome DevTools endpoint.\"\n          },\n          \"userDataDir\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile User Data Dir\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile Chromium user data directory for existing-session attachment through Chrome DevTools MCP. Use this for Brave, Edge, Chromium, or non-default Chrome profiles when the built-in auto-connect path would pick the wrong browser data directory on the selected host or browser node. Paths starting with ~ expand to the OS home directory.\"\n          },\n          \"mcpCommand\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Chrome MCP Command\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile Chrome DevTools MCP command for existing-session attachment. Defaults to npx.\"\n          },\n          \"mcpArgs\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Chrome MCP Args\",\n            \"description\": \"Extra per-profile Chrome DevTools MCP arguments for existing-session attachment, such as --no-usage-statistics. Endpoint arguments here override the built-in auto-connect or browser URL selection.\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"driver\": {\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Driver\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile browser driver mode. Use \\\"openclaw\\\" (or legacy \\\"clawd\\\") for CDP-based profiles, or use \\\"existing-session\\\" for Chrome DevTools MCP attachment on the selected host or browser node.\",\n            \"anyOf\": [\n              {\n                \"type\": \"string\",\n                \"const\": \"openclaw\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"type\": \"string\",\n                \"const\": \"clawd\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"type\": \"string\",\n                \"const\": \"existing-session\"\n              }\n            ]\n          },\n          \"headless\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Headless Mode\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile headless override for locally launched browser instances. Use this when one profile should stay headless without forcing browser.headless for every other profile.\"\n          },\n          \"executablePath\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Executable Path\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile browser executable path for locally launched managed browser profiles. Overrides browser.executablePath and accepts paths starting with ~ for the OS home directory.\"\n          },\n          \"attachOnly\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Attach-only Mode\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile attach-only override that skips local browser launch and only attaches to an existing CDP endpoint. Useful when one profile is externally managed but others are locally launched.\"\n          },\n          \"color\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"pattern\": \"^#?[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$\",\n            \"title\": \"Browser Profile Accent Color\",\n            \"description\": \"Per-profile accent color for visual differentiation in dashboards and browser-related UI hints. Use distinct colors for high-signal operator recognition of active profiles.\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"reloadKind\": \"restart\",\n    \"hint\": {\n      \"label\": \"Browser Profiles\",\n      \"help\": \"Named browser profile connection map used for explicit routing to CDP ports or URLs with optional metadata. Keep profile names consistent and avoid overlapping endpoint definitions.\",\n      \"tags\": [\n        \"storage\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"hintPath\": \"browser.profiles\",\n    \"children\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"*\",\n        \"path\": \"browser.profiles.*\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"restart\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"result":{"path":"browser.profiles","schema":{"type":"object","title":"Browser Profiles","description":"Named browser profile connection map used for explicit routing to CDP ports or URLs with optional metadata. Keep profile names consistent and avoid overlapping endpoint definitions.","additionalProperties":{"type":"object","additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"cdpPort":{"type":"integer","minimum":1,"maximum":65535,"title":"Browser Profile CDP Port","description":"Per-profile local CDP port used when connecting to browser instances by port instead of URL. Use unique ports per profile to avoid connection collisions."},"cdpUrl":{"type":"string","title":"Browser Profile CDP URL","description":"Per-profile CDP/DevTools endpoint URL used for explicit browser routing by profile name. Use this for remote CDP hosts, tunnels, or existing-session profiles that should attach through a running Chrome DevTools endpoint."},"userDataDir":{"type":"string","title":"Browser Profile User Data Dir","description":"Per-profile Chromium user data directory for existing-session attachment through Chrome DevTools MCP. Use this for Brave, Edge, Chromium, or non-default Chrome profiles when the built-in auto-connect path would pick the wrong browser data directory on the selected host or browser node. Paths starting with ~ expand to the OS home directory."},"mcpCommand":{"type":"string","title":"Browser Profile Chrome MCP Command","description":"Per-profile Chrome DevTools MCP command for existing-session attachment. Defaults to npx."},"mcpArgs":{"type":"array","title":"Browser Profile Chrome MCP Args","description":"Extra per-profile Chrome DevTools MCP arguments for existing-session attachment, such as --no-usage-statistics. Endpoint arguments here override the built-in auto-connect or browser URL selection.","items":{"type":"string"}},"driver":{"title":"Browser Profile Driver","description":"Per-profile browser driver mode. Use \"openclaw\" (or legacy \"clawd\") for CDP-based profiles, or use \"existing-session\" for Chrome DevTools MCP attachment on the selected host or browser node.","anyOf":[{"type":"string","const":"openclaw"},{"type":"string","const":"clawd"},{"type":"string","const":"existing-session"}]},"headless":{"type":"boolean","title":"Browser Profile Headless Mode","description":"Per-profile headless override for locally launched browser instances. Use this when one profile should stay headless without forcing browser.headless for every other profile."},"executablePath":{"type":"string","title":"Browser Profile Executable Path","description":"Per-profile browser executable path for locally launched managed browser profiles. Overrides browser.executablePath and accepts paths starting with ~ for the OS home directory."},"attachOnly":{"type":"boolean","title":"Browser Profile Attach-only Mode","description":"Per-profile attach-only override that skips local browser launch and only attaches to an existing CDP endpoint. Useful when one profile is externally managed but others are locally launched."},"color":{"type":"string","pattern":"^#?[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$","title":"Browser Profile Accent Color","description":"Per-profile accent color for visual differentiation in dashboards and browser-related UI hints. Use distinct colors for high-signal operator recognition of active profiles."}}}},"reloadKind":"restart","hint":{"label":"Browser Profiles","help":"Named browser profile connection map used for explicit routing to CDP ports or URLs with optional metadata. Keep profile names consistent and avoid overlapping endpoint definitions.","tags":["storage"]},"hintPath":"browser.profiles","children":[{"key":"*","path":"browser.profiles.*","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"reloadKind":"restart"}]}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782368195589}}
{"type":"message","id":"0987d596","parentId":"9699b306","timestamp":"2026-06-25T06:16:44.219Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**字段确认完毕。** OpenClaw 6.9 的 `browser.profiles.*` 支持：\n- `cdpPort`、`cdpUrl`、`userDataDir`、`color`（你截图里那些都对）\n- 还多了 `headless`、`executablePath`、`attachOnly`、`driver`、`mcpCommand`、`mcpArgs`\n\n**注意：profile 对象里没有 `label` 字段**——截图里那个 `\"label\"` 是别人 schema 加的扩展，我们**不能用**。我去掉。\n\n---\n\n## 🪶 开工：HUG-VN profile 写入 openclaw.json\n\n**配置：**\n- profile name: `tk-HUG-VN`\n- cdpPort: **18901**（截图里 18801/18802 已被占）\n- color: **#A155F0**（紫色 = Heat Up Glow 时尚感）\n- userDataDir: `/home/halei/.openclaw/browser/tk-HUG-VN`\n- headless: **false**（你 14:02 选的可视化）\n\n先建 profile 目录，然后改 openclaw.json。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hteey1d3bn1v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/halei/.openclaw/browser/tk-HUG-VN\nls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/browser/tk-HUG-VN/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hteey1d3bn1v_2","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.patch","raw":"{\n  \"browser\": {\n    \"headless\": false,\n    \"defaultProfile\": \"tk-HUG-VN\",\n    \"profiles\": {\n      \"tk-HUG-VN\": {\n        \"userDataDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/browser/tk-HUG-VN\",\n        \"cdpPort\": 18901,\n        \"color\": \"#A155F0\",\n        \"headless\": false\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}","reason":"添加 TK HUG-VN 浏览器 profile（Heat Up Glow - VN 发饰店铺）","note":"已添加 tk-HUG-VN 浏览器 profile，重启后生效"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":1032,"output":464,"cacheRead":90155,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91651,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782368195610,"responseId":"068bfac45a5e374c1979cc819ea72b76","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
